Ahhhh throwback thursdays. Thinking of my great pal the always gorgeous @deniserichards this morning. Unbelievable that we met on #starshiptroopers1996, then we were a zany couple in #tailLightsFade, 1998, then in 2006 “sex,love & secrets” on WB for a year. This pic is from a super cute lil movie called “Dally and Spanky”, 2019 a true story about a jack russell terrier and a Donkey who are best friends. And yes, every show we’ve shared and worked together has been wonderful. Denise has been through a ton of life’s slings and arrows, and yet she’s always got a smile, and the BEST laugh! Belly laughs! I loved working on TLF with her. My goal was to keep her laughing all day. Big belly laughs. Sometimes in the film you can see that her eye makeup would be smudged from the laugh tears, haha. So fun! Sometimes we need to revel in the great memories. So on this great TB Thursday, here’s to my pal, and onscreen GF, miss @deniserichards . Luv ya gal! 😘🥰😎

Good NEWS! For all of you @aprilhutchinson1 fans out there, yesterday her pancreas tumor was removed along with her spleen. We are praying that this is the end of cancer for her! Her surgeon was proud of the work they did, and she’s resting with the good folks at #uclamedicalcenter . Thank you for your support and kind words!! Go April 💪🙏🏼🙏🏼
Hey there! We are wanting to raise money for Autumn to go on a field trip to England, a little worldliness never hurts a curious young mind. I hope your day is splendid !

My lifelong love, April Hutchinson, has been battling cancer since 2018. We spent the pandemic by kicking off lockdown with a double mastectomy. The healing was a long time. She was alone in hospital the first 5 days of it due to draconian covid protocols. She came home and proceeded to endure a year of Chemo, then 6mos radiation, then was cleared of cancer and had an attempted Brest reconstruction. The Doc’s fouled that up and then demanded $186,000 out of pocket (we no have! ) and about a year later, it was determined that she had pancreatic cancer and another tumor in her liver. She just did 4 months of hospital time and then 4 months of chemo. Last week she capped it off with a tumorectomy of the pancreas and has a radioactive bead in her liver tumor. Still want that cocktail, my friend? Lol Anyway. She’s on the mend from the last surgery. She’s home now and Autumn is just elated to have mama back at home. And I’m happy for them too, and glad to be here to help, …but  we need one more thing. A little love from you my friend,  sent in her direction. Just take a minute. Look at her beautiful countenance on @aprilhutchinson1 or my page take a deep breath and think happy thoughts of she being healed. She’s my baby’s mama and the best mama, at that!  Have a wonderful blessed day, my friend. 👍🏼🙏🏼❤️ thank you thank you.

Mama is recovering well. Thanks for all the healing vibes!!! One more thing… would you give a dollar for a life altering awareness and education trip for Autumn ? She’s been so good taking care of mama for the last 4/5 years. Basically the second half of her life to this point. And I want to broaden her horizons and take her to England on a birthday trip. Would you be cool with a buck ? And maybe it the other 90,000 folks on here add a buck she’ll get to go with me. (OMG could you imagine?! Lol ) but we can’t all afford to part with a dollar these days so i know it’s a big thing. But Autumn would really appreciate such a warm birthday wish ! 👍👍👍👍 https://gofund.me/90f7f1f0

Hey howdy my friend. Oh my oh my, how life is so fun. So- I’m headed to a much needed work trip, and it’s on my daughters 11th birthday weekend. Trying to be a good dad, I want to take her with me and let her mama heal from the cancer surgeries. The problem is- i will  only earn about 1/2 the cost of airfare for her….so it isn’t feasible without help from - -a little less than 10,000 friends. So…….Would you help a kid gain some worldly experience before middle school?, and donate $1.00 to the “Autumn goes to England”
Fund? Just Yesterday her doc told us it’s mentally unhealthy for her to be by her mothers side 24/7 and a caretaker at the age of 10. Lately She’s enduring massive abdominal pains, and a lot of other unmentionables here, due to the stress of seeing mama go thru this cancer battle for the last 5 years. Her mother is an Aries, & doesn’t approve of this message-  but her doctor says she needs to be out in the world and not sitting in bed caring for mama. Apparently not good for the psyche of a 10 year old. And embarrassingly, this is why I Ask, Could you please help with donating a dollar? My work trip is the 7/27-31st. I want to take her with me and show her the country she is so enamored with. UK. (And she does a wicked Manchester accent). Please don’t donate much! , but perhaps tell a friend? Idk. I don’t want to inconvenience anyone. But with 95,000 followers i thought maybe a few folks could help make it happen. And i really appreciate it🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼. Even 50c & 20,0000 people. .. I want her to see England and enjoy a bit of fun and excitement beyond the iPad /couch scene. . We’ve ALL been hit by covid and it’s tough as hell to recover. A nightmare scene for sure. So thank you, (the village raises the child after all. ) please help Autumn get to see the UK for a dollar out of your pocket. 🙏😊

“I don’t understand why we haven’t been driving hydrogen-powered cars for the last 30 years”

Well, this is an interesting one. Glad changes are being made. The heightened fear of guns on set after the accident has permeated all sets I’ve worked on since, and we just don’t need the “what if” factor anymore. It’s not the 1960’s. Culture has changed. Kids don’t get red rider BB guns for Christmas like we did. Cowboys aren’t heroes killing native Americans. The world is different, we’ve matured, and it’s good that the film industry is taking a step in a needed direction. We finished Rust at the end of may, in Montana. The experience was amazing and I can’t wait to see the film, as a lot of emotions went into this one. I didn’t know Halyna but I know a lot of her friends, and this film was finished with the utmost effort to pay homage and respect to her while exhibiting and sharing her last work with the world. She was an amazing woman from those I’ve spoken to. I’m so sorry to have not met her and though it is tragic, her memory is forever preserved in this film. We finished it in her honor. In somber mind, with loving hearts. It was a close and dedicated crew.  https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/25/arts/rust-killing-forces-hollywood-to-make-choices-on-guns.html?smid=url-share
